INSERT INTO `tourism_tm_destination` VALUES (32,1,'desa-wae-rebo','Desa Wae Rebo','Wae Rebo Village',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: Open Sans, sans-serif;\">Desa tradisional Wae Rebo di distrik Manggarai di pulau Flores, Nusa Tenggara Timur, telah menerima Top Award of Excellence dari UNESCO dalam Penghargaan Warisan Asia Pasifik UNESCO 2012, yang diumumkan di Bangkok pada 27 Agustus 2012.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: Open Sans, sans-serif;\">Desa kecil dan terpencil ini dikenal atas pembangunan kembali rumah adat Mbaru Niang yang dilandasi semangat kerjasama masyarakat menuju tradisi yang lestari, sekaligus meningkatkan kesejahteraan desanya.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: Open Sans, sans-serif;\">Ciri utama Wae Rebo adalah rumah mereka yang unik, yang mereka sebut Mbaru Niang yang tinggi dan berbentuk kerucut dan seluruhnya tertutup lontar lontar dari atapnya hingga ke tanah. Tampaknya pada suatu waktu rumah semacam itu cukup umum di wilayah tersebut. Namun saat ini, hanya desa inilah yang tetap mempertahankan rumah adat khas Manggarai, tanpanya rumah-rumah unik tersebut pasti akan tersapu habis.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">The traditional village of Wae Rebo in the district of Manggarai on the island of&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; color: #0275d8; text-decoration-line: none; touch-action: manipulation; white-space: pre-wrap; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\" href=\"https://www.indonesia.travel/content/indtravelrevamp/gb/en/destinations/bali-nusa-tenggara/flores.html\">Flores</a><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">, East Nusatenggara, has received the Top Award of Excellence from UNESCO in the 2012 UNESCO Asia Pacific Heritage Awards, announced in Bangkok on 27 August 2012.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">This small and isolated village was recognized for its rebuilding of the traditional Mbaru Niang traditional house based on the spirit of community cooperation towards a sustainable tradition, while at the same time improving its village welfare.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #292b2c; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Wae Rebo&rsquo;s main characteristics are their unique houses, which they call Mbaru Niang that are tall and conical in shape and are completely covered in lontar thatch from its rooftop down to the ground.&nbsp; It appears that at one time such kind of houses were quite common to the region. But today, it is only this village that continues to maintain the typical Manggarai traditional house, without which these unique houses would have been completely fazed out.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20200924130424.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo','wae@rebo','08:00 AM','09796786678','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-09-24 13:04:24','2020-12-03 05:33:58'),(33,1,'bukit-amelia-sea','Bukit Amelia Sea','Amelia Sea Hill',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>Memang Provinsi Nusa Tenggara Timur terkenal dengan Pulau Komodo-nya. Namun, banyak atraksi lain yang tersedia di kawasan ini. Misalnya, ada Amelia Sea View yang terletak di Labuan Bajo. Seperti namanya, ini adalah lokasi untuk menikmati pemandangan laut yang menakjubkan termasuk matahari terbit dan terbenam. Tempat wisata ini terletak di atas bukit hijau, tempat para wisatawan bersantai dan menikmati alam dengan penuh semangat. Karena letaknya yang strategis, bukit ini juga memancarkan suasana yang menyegarkan. Berkat udara yang masih alami !.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>It is true East Nusa Tenggara Province is famous for its Komodo Island. However, many other attractions are available in this region. For instance, there is Amelia Sea View located in Labuan Bajo. As the name suggests, it is the location to enjoy stunning sea views including the sunrise and sunset. This sightseeing spot is situated on a green hill, on which tourists relax and enjoy the nature passionately. Due to its strategic location, the hill also emits a refreshing atmosphere. Thanks to the unspoiled air!.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20200924131911.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/st-d_Ry4DEM','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 28px; font-size: 14px; color: #666666; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000;\">Fasilitas</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 28px; font-size: 14px; color: #666666; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Tidak ada akomodasi di Gili Laba. Jika Anda ingin menyewa kamar, sebaiknya Anda melakukannya di Labuan Bajo.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 28px; font-size: 14px; color: #666666; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000;\">Menuju Lokasi</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; line-height: 28px; font-size: 14px; color: #666666; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Gili Laba adalah sebuah pulau kecil dan bagian dari Pulau Sumbawa. Anda bisa mencapainya dari Labuan Bajo. Dibutuhkan 4 jam untuk Gili Laba menggunakan speedboat. Sebenarnya, dimungkinkan untuk mengunjungi Gili Laba dari Pulau Komodo. Dari sini dibutuhkan waktu satu jam. Perjalanan terasa nyaman dan menyenangkan.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','West Manggarai','amelia@sea','08:00 AM','0899876756','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-09-24 13:19:11','2021-01-19 11:37:48'),(34,1,'bukit-cinta-labuan-bajo','Bukit Cinta Labuan Bajo','Love Hill Labuan Bajo',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Labuan Bajo yang kaya akan wisata baharinya, memiliki spot romantis di sebuah bukit yang bernama Bukit Cinta. Bukit Cinta Labuan Bajo sering dijadikan tujuan untuk menghabiskan waktu bersama, menikmati pemandangan dan juga berfoto.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Nama Bukit Cinta diberikan karena tempat ini memang merupakan spot yang tepat untuk pengunjung memadu kasih dan memang banyak pasangan muda-mudi yang menghabiskan waktu di bukit ini pada malam harinya.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Laut di kejauhan berwarna biru gelap nan indah berpadu dengan warna biru langit dan bukit yang berwarna kehijauan. Mirip gambar di kartu pos. Sangat indah meski Anda bakal berkeringat berdiri di atas bukit.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Pesona Bukit Cinta ini membuat pengunjungnya ingin kembali lagi ke tempat ini. Menyaksikan langit dengan semburat warna oranye keemasan atau kerap disebut sebagai golden sunset kala senja tentu akan menjadi pengalaman yang sangat menyenangkan.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Inilah salah satu spot yang wajib didatangi di Labuan Bajo. Tidak afdhol jika objek wisata ini terlewatkan. Bukit Cinta berada di dataran Labuan Bajo, Manggarai Barat, Flores Barat. Indah dan Instagramble. Banyak obyek panorama alam yang bisa diambil.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>Labuan Bajo, which is rich in marine tourism, has a romantic spot on a hill called Bukit Cinta. Bukit Cinta Labuan Bajo is often used as a destination to spend time together, enjoy the scenery and also take pictures.</p>\r\n<p>The name Bukit Cinta was given because this place is indeed the right spot for visitors to make love and indeed many young couples spend time on this hill at night.</p>\r\n<p>The sea in the distance is a beautiful dark blue combined with the blue sky and green hills. It looks like a picture on a postcard. Very beautiful even though you will sweat standing on the hill.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The charm of Bukit Cinta makes visitors want to come back to this place. Watching the sky with a golden orange tinge or often referred to as the golden sunset at dusk will certainly be a very pleasant experience.</p>\r\n<p>This is one of the spots that must be visited in Labuan Bajo. Don\'t afdhol if this tourist attraction is missed. Bukit Cinta is located in the plains of Labuan Bajo, West Manggarai, West Flores. Beautiful and Instagramble. Many natural panorama objects that can be taken.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20200924132446.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/00blpTSF-H0','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Menuju lokasi ini tak sulit, hanya sekitar 10 menit perjalanan darat dari kota Labuan Bajo. Di bukit ini, hanya ilalang setinggi 30 cm yang membentang sepanjang bukit. Kalau malam hari, bukit ini gelap gulita karena belum ada penerangan.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Meski begitu, ada banyak spot yang layak untuk menjadi objek foto. Bila kuat, bisa melakukan trekking ringan menuju puncak bukit. Jalannya tidak terlalu terjam, namun tetap harus hati-hati karena medannya yang berbatu.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Kalau tak kuat, di bukit yang ada di bawah Bukit Cinta bagus juga untuk lokasi pemotretan. Naik ke puncak mungkin membutuh waktu 10-15 menit. Kalau napas ngos-ngosan, lebih baik di bawah bukit saja.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Namun meskipun demikian, perjalanan trekking tidak akan terasa membosankan sama sekali karena pengunjung dapat meluangkan waktu sejenak untuk sekedar mengambil foto atau menikmati semilir angin yang berhembus.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px #ffffff; color: #666666; font-family: \'Open Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\">Deretan pohon aren akan jadi teman sepanjang perjalanan trekking menuju ke atas bukit. Laut nan biru, pemandangan Kota Labuan Bajo, deretan pepohonan dan bukit-bukit hijau akan memanjakan mata setiap pengunjung bukit ini.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo, Komodo, West Manggarai Regency, East Nusa Tenggara','bukit@cinta','08:00 AM','089878678','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-09-24 13:24:46','2020-12-03 05:37:19'),(35,1,'pulau-komodo','Pulau Komodo','Komodo Island',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Saat Anda sedang memikirkan destinasi wisata di Labuan Bajo, Pulau Komodo pasti jadi salah satu pulau yang wajib Anda kunjungi. Berada di sebelah timur Pulau Sumbawa dan dipisahkan oleh Selat Sape, Pulau Komodo merupakan salah satu habitat asli hewan komodo.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Taman Nasional Komodo saat ini telah dikelola oleh pemerintah pusat dan ditetapkan sebagai sebuah cagar biosfer dan situs warisan budaya oleh UNESCO. Tujuan utamanya adalah untuk mengkonservasi hubungan antara Komodo dengan habitatnya, serta melindungi keanekaragaman hayati baik di darat maupun di laut. Hingga tahun 2020, di pulau ini tercatat sekitar &hellip; ekor komodo.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Selain komodo, Taman Nasional Komodo juga merupakan rumah dari spesies unik lainnya serta kekayaan biota laut seperti terumbu karang, rumput laut, serta ikan warna-warni yang menemani sesi menyelam Anda. Jadi, selain bisa bersantai sambil menikmati kekayaan alam, Anda juga bisa menikmati serunya menyelam di laut.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Jika Anda tertarik untuk mengunjungi Pulau Komodo, ada beberapa hal yang harus Anda perhatikan demi kenyamanan dan keamanan saat berkunjung.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Do\'s:</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">1. Gunakan pakaian yang nyaman serta dapat menyerap keringat.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">2. Sebaiknya Anda menggunakan pakaian lengan panjang, celana panjang serta topi untuk melindungi Anda dari sengatan matahari dan serangga.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">3. Disarankan untuk menggunakan sepatu dan kacamata hitam.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">4. Perhatikan petunjuk, karena ada beberapa lokasi yang meminta Anda untuk melepas sepatu dan memakai pakaian yang sopan sebagai bentuk penghormatan.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">5. Jangan lupa bawa </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">sunscreen, sunblock, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">obat-obatan, salep anti serangga, dan </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">first-aird kit.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ll of diving in the wondrous sea.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-a33415ce-7fff-8935-8f7b-c354dca327a2\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you are interested to visit Komodo Island, there are several things that you should pay attention to for the sake of your own comfort and safety while enjoying the island:</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">1. Use clothes that are comfortable and can absorb sweat.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">2. We recommend you to wear long sleeves, trousers and a hat to protect yourself from sunburn and insects.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">3. It is recommended to wear shoes and sunglasses.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">4. Pay attention to the instructions. For example, there are several locations that ask you to take off your shoes and wear modest clothes as a form of respect.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">5. Don\'t forget to bring sunscreen, sunblock</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">medication, insect spray, and first-aid kit</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201130045506.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Pulau Komodo, Kabupaten Manggarai Barat, Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 04:55:06','2021-01-20 13:08:30'),(36,1,'pulau-padar','Pulau Padar','Padar Island',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Selain Pulau Komodo, masih banyak harta karun destinasi wisata yang tak kalah mempesona mata. Salah satunya adalah Pulau Padar. Secara geografis, Pulau Padar relatif lebih dekat dengan Pulau Rinca dibandingkan Pulau Komodo, yang dipisahkan oleh Selat Lintah.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-e40d5161-7fff-06a3-05d6-6a4027ab4608\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pulau Padar juga merupakan salah satu warisan dari UNESCO karena masih berada di kawasan Taman Nasional Komodo. Bedanya adalah, Pulau Padar tidak dihuni oleh </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ora</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> atau biawak komodo. Di dalam Pulau Padar, terdiri dari tiga - empat pulau kecil di sekelilingnya.</span><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Jika di Pulau Komodo, Anda akan bebas menikmati berinteraksi dengan komodo. Di Pulau Padar, Anda akan bebas menikmati keindahan dari tiga pantai dengan warna pasir yang berbeda-beda: Ada pasir merah muda, hitam, dan juga putih. Pulau Padar memang terkenal karena memiliki titik terbaik untuk menikmati keindahan lanskap di sekitarnya karena memberikan ciri khas tersendiri akan panorama yang dimiliki. Tapi, untuk menikmati ketiga pulau secara langsung, Anda diharuskan untuk trekking kurang lebih 45 menit - 1 jam. Anda tidak perlu khawatir, karena semuanya akan terbayar dengan pemandangan yang mempesona.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Karena lokasinya yang masih sama di kawasan Taman Nasional Komodo, tentu ada beberapa peraturan yang harus Anda perhatikan demi kenyamanan bersama. Dan satu lagi, jangan lupa untuk membawa sepatu trekking, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">sunblock, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">dan juga pakaian yang nyaman, ya.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Not only Komodo Island, there are also lots of other tourist destinations that are no less dazzling to the eye. One of them is Padar Island. Geographically, Padar Island is closer to Rinca Island than Komodo Island, which is separated by the Lintah Strait.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-90bee4f8-7fff-a599-dbcc-4285949f7863\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Padar Island is also a UNESCO heritage because it\'s a part of the Komodo National Park area. The difference is, Padar Island is not inhabited by </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ora</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> or komodo dragon lizards. Padar Island itself consists of 3 - 4 small islands around it.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">On Komodo Island you are free to watch the Komodo dragons. On the other hand, Padar Island offers you something else. There you will be free to be amused by the beauty of three beaches with different sand colors; pink, black and white sand. Padar Island is indeed famous because it has the best point to enjoy the view of the surrounding landscape.&nbsp; It gives its own characteristic of the panorama that this island has. However, to enjoy the three islands directly, you are required to do trekking for approximately 45 - 60 minutes. It may take quite a long time, but you don\'t need to worry as in the end everything will pay off with an enchanting view.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Because its location is still in the Komodo National Park area, of course there are several regulations that you must pay attention to for mutual comfort. And one more thing, don\'t forget to bring trekking shoes, sunblock,</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">and also wear a comfortable clothes.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201130053231.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>Work in progress</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Pulau Padar, Labuan Bajo, Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 05:32:31','2021-01-20 13:08:44'),(37,1,'pantai-pink','Pantai Pink','Pink Beach',NULL,' <!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sesuai dengan namanya, Pantai Pink atau dikenal dengan Pink Beach ini memiliki warna pink. Sebenarnya, warna pink tersebut berasal dari hewan berukuran mikroskopis bernama Foraminifera yang kemudian memberikan pigmen merah pada koral. Koral-koral tersebut terbawa oleh gelombang menuju pesisir lalu hancur menjadi serpihan dan butiran yang kini menjadi pasir pantai. Warna pink ini juga tidak hanya berada di satu titik saja, melainkan sepanjang Pulau Komodo.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pink Beach</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> terletak di dalam kawasan Taman Nasional Komodo merupakan destinasi wisatawan yang menarik dan patut untuk dikunjungi. Pantai ini dipercaya merupakan salah satu dari hanya tujuh pantai di dunia yang memiliki pasir pantai berwarna pink. Pantai ini begitu tenang dan hanya memiliki ombak yang kecil sehingga membuat wisatawan lebih nyaman ketika snorkeling sambil menikmati kekayaan biota bawah laut. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">As the name implies, Pink Beach has pink color sand. In fact, the pink color comes from a microscopic animal called </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Foraminifera</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> which then gives the red pigment to the coral. The corals are carried by the waves towards the coast and then crushed into shreds and grains which now become beach sand. This pink color is not only at one point, but also along the Komodo Island.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9f9f9466-7fff-0434-103e-477a007e66ec\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pink Beach, located within the Komodo National Park area, is an attractive tourist destination and worth visiting. This beach is believed to be one of only seven beaches in the world that has pink sand beaches. It is so calm and only has small waves so that it makes tourists more comfortable when snorkeling and enjoying the magnificence underwater life.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','  <!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201203151450.png',NULL,' <!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>',' <!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>',' <!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Pantai Merah (Pink Beach)','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 06:50:13','2021-01-20 13:09:30'),(38,1,'manta-point','Manta Point','Manta Point',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Jika Anda termasuk salah satu pecinta aktivitas snorkeling atau menyelam, pastikan Manta Point menjadi destinasi yang Anda wajib dikunjungi saat berkunjung ke Labuan Bajo. Saat menyelam di Manta Point, Anda bisa menikmati berbagai kekayaan ekosistem laut yang eksotis dan mempesona, dan yang paling penting Anda bisa berkesempatan bertemu dengan Manta Ray, salah satu satwa air yang langka dan dilindungi khas Indonesia.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-a062b299-7fff-2c0a-fdb9-c7aed740644d\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Dimana ada Manta, disitu ada ubur-ubur. Hal ini dikarenakan ubur-ubur merupakan makanan utama dari ikan Manta. Yang artinya, jika Anda melihat segerombolan manta sedang berkumpul itu menandakan mereka telah menemukan ubur-ubur yang siap disantap. Sungguh pengalaman yang menarik bukan?</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Karena pemandangan bawah laut yang sangat menawan, penting untuk Anda membawa kamera anti air sehingga Anda bisa bebas mengabadikan momen bawah laut bersama ikan Manta dan ikan lainnya. Bagi Anda yang ingin berkunjung, tidak perlu khawatir karena semua perlengkapan snorkeling mulai dari masker, fin, pelampung, sampai tabung gas telah disediakan oleh pengelola wisata. Anda bisa bertanya langsung di lokasi terkait biaya sewa dan kebutuhan lainnya.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">So, you are into a snorkeling or diving activity? make sure Manta Point is on your destination list if you come to Labuan Bajo. When you dive at Manta Point, you can enjoy a variety of exotic and fascinating marine ecosystems, and most importantly you can have the opportunity to meet Manta Ray, one of Indonesia\'s rare and protected aquatic animals.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-1b7a54c3-7fff-73b2-3716-038cf6bb7f49\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Where there are Manta fish, there will also be jellyfish in your sight. This is because jellyfish are the main food of Manta fish. Which means, if you see a swarm of mantas gathering, it indicates they have found jellyfish that are ready to eat. It\'s really an interesting experience, right?</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Here, the underwater scenery is very captivating. So it is important that you bring a waterproof camera to freely capture the underwater moments with the rare Manta fish and other fish. For those of you who want to visit, you don\'t need to worry because all the snorkeling equipment such as masks, fins, buoys and gas cylinders will be provided by the tour manager. You can ask directly on the spot regarding rental fees and other needs.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201203151814.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Pulau Komodo, Kabupaten Manggarai Barat, Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 06:52:48','2020-12-23 01:22:28'),(39,1,'pulau-kalong','Pulau Kalong','Kalong Island',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Mulai dari kekayaan hayati, keindahan laut, hamparan pasir pantai, sampai berbagai macam hewan memang bisa Anda jumpai saat berkunjung ke Nusa Tenggara Timur. Tidak cukup berkunjung dalam satu kurun waktu, Nusa Tenggara Timur memang menyimpan surga dunia yang tidak ada habisnya. Tidak heran, banyak wisatawan baik dari domestik maupun mancanegara yang terpikat dengan pesona alamnya yang begitu indah.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-3384330d-7fff-dd19-55c4-2ce8fd88d804\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Berbicara soal kekayaan alam, Pulau Kalong menjadi salah satu destinasi wisata terbaik yang berada tidak jauh dari Taman Nasional Komodo. Jika biasanya Anda bertemu dengan pantai dan pantai, di sini Anda akan bertemu deretan pohon eksotis yang menjadi habitat besar oleh jutaan kelelawar raksasa atau kalong. Selain itu, Pulau Kalong juga menjadi lokasi wisata yang memiliki pemandangan matahari terbenam paling indah di Taman Nasional Komodo.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ketika sunset tiba akan ada kawanan kelelawar atau kalong yang terbang dalam jumlah&nbsp; sangat banyak sehingga pasti menimbulkan decak kagum bagi yang melihatnya. Untuk itu, waktu yang paling tepat untuk menyaksikan pemandangan ini adalah sekitar pukul 6 sore. Tapi perlu hati-hati karena lokasinya yang penuh dengan pohon dan semak ilalang, keselamatan pengunjung menjadi hal yang utama. Jika Anda tetap ingin menyaksikan pemandangan matahari terbenam, silakan menghubungi pengelola wisata setempat supaya mendapatkan pengawasan dan pengamanan.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-8c67b1ca-7fff-1af5-2647-52a45e25196d\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Starting from its biological richness, the beauty of the sea, the stretch of beach sand, to various kinds of animals; all of them you can indeed encounter when visiting East Nusa Tenggara. It feels like one time is not enough to explore them, as East Nusa Tenggara has an endless world of paradise. Is not a surprise that many tourists, both domestic and foreign, are captivated by its beautiful natural charm.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Talking about natural wealth, Kalong Island is one of the best tourist destinations located not far from Komodo National Park. If you usually meet oceans and beaches, here you will meet a row of exotic trees that are a large habitat for millions of giant </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kalong</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, the local name for bats. Furthermore, Kalong Island is also a tourist location that has the most beautiful sunset views in Komodo National Park.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">When the sunset arrives, there will be a large number of bats flying. That scenery will definitely amaze those who see it. For this reason, the best time to witness this sight is around 6 in the afternoon. But you need to be careful. The location is full of trees and weeds, so the safety of visitors is an important thing. If you still want to watch the sunset view, please contact the local tour manager for supervision and security.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201130065741.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>',NULL,'s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 06:57:41','2020-12-23 01:23:23'),(44,1,'gua-batu-cermin','Gua Batu Cermin','Batu Cermin Cave',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Belum lengkap rasanya kalau tidak mampir menyusuri Gua Batu Cermin saat berkunjung ke Labuan Bajo. Gua Batu Cermin adalah salah satu obyek wisata unik di Labuan Bajo. Gua yang terdapat di bukit batu yang gelap ini memiliki luas sekitar 19 hektar dan tinggi sekitar 75 meter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sinar matahari masuk ke dalam gua dan dipantulkan melalui dinding-dinding sehingga merefleksikan cahaya kecil ke area lain dalam gua dan menciptakan ilusi seperti cermin. Stalagtit dan stalagmit dalam gua terlihat berkilauan saat disinari cahaya senter maupun cahaya matahari. Kilauan ini disebabkan oleh kandungan garam di dalam air yang mengalir saat turun hujan. Inilah yang membuat masyarakat sekitar menyebut gua ini dengan nama Gua Batu Cermin.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Gua Batu Cermin akan ramai dikunjungi para wisatawan di pagi hari, sekitar pukul 9 hingga pukul 10. Karena pada jam inilah adalah waktu terbaik dimana penunjung bisa melihat dengan jelas dinding goa dari pantulan sinar matahari yang menakjubkan. Selain itu, Anda juga bisa menikmati lingkungan yang asri, sejuk, dan tenang di sekeliling batu cermin.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bagi Anda pecinta fotografi, Anda bisa dengan puas memfoto berbagai objek cantik di dalam gua. Tidak hanya itu, Anda juga bisa berpapasan dengan monyet atau hewan lainnya yang bisa Anda abadikan momen indahnya.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Your visit at Labuan Bajo is incomplete if you don\'t stop by at Batu Cermin Cave. Batu Cermin Cave is one of the exotic tourist attractions in Labuan Bajo. The cave, which is located in a hill of dark rock, has an area of ​​about 19 hectares and a height of about 75 meters.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-43732d00-7fff-b09e-d1d5-21a2a98a4b67\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">When sunlight enters the cave and is reflected through the walls so that it reflects small lights to other areas of the cave and creates a mirror-like illusion. The stalactites and stalagmites in the cave are sparkling when exposed to flashlights or sunlight. This sparkle is caused by the salt content in the flowing water when it rains. This is what makes the local community call this cave by the name Batu Cermin Cave.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Batu Cermin Cave will be crowded with tourists around 9 to 10 in the morning, because this is the best time for visitors to see the walls of the cave clearly from the amazing reflection of the sun. As well as that, you can also enjoy the stunning, cool, and calm environment around the mirror stone.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">For you, photography lovers, you will be satisfied taking pictures of various beautiful objects in the cave. Not only that, you can also run into monkeys or other animals that you can capture the beautiful moments of.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201210082804.png','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo, Manggarai Barat, Flores, Nusa Tenggara Timur, Indonesia','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4',1,'2020-11-30 07:20:24','2020-12-23 01:25:04'),(45,1,'gua-rangko','Gua Rangko','Rangko Cave',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Selain Gua Batu Cermin, ada Gua Rangko yang menjadi alternatif lain saat berkunjung ke Labuan Bajo. Sama indahnya dengan Gua Batu Cermin, Gua Rangko dapat diibaratkan sebagai sebuah kolam renang pribadi yang menawarkan keheningan bagi Anda yang datang. Air yang terdapat di dalam gua tersebut merupakan air asin dan bersumber dari air laut yang masuk melalui rongga-rongga atau celah yang menghubungkan kolam di dalam gua dengan laut lepas.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pada bagian atas Gua Rangko juga terdapat orname stalaktit yang sangat cantik dan menawan. Untuk mencapai ke Gua Rangko dibutuhkan waktu tempuh sekitar 1 jam dari Labuan Bajo ke Desa Rangko. Setelah itu Anda akan disambut oleh penduduk lokal yang menawarkan jasa kapal boat untuk menyeberang ke Gua Rangko. Karena jalanannya yang berbatu dan tanahnya yang cukup licin, Anda perlu berhati-hati dan disarankan untuk tidak menggunakan sandal. Gua Rangko memiliki waktu spesial untuk menikmati pemandangannya, yakni sekitar pukul 12.00 - 14.00, untuk itu sebaiknya Anda berangkat sepagi mungkin dari Labuan Bajo supaya tidak ketinggalan momennya.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Aside from Batu Cermin Cave, there is Rangko Cave, another alternative place when visiting Labuan Bajo. As gorgeous as Batu Cermin Cave, Rangko Cave can be likened to a private swimming pool that offers serenity for those of you who come. The water in the cave is salt water and comes from sea water that enters through the cavities or gaps that connect the pools in the cave with the open sea.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-628bfb62-7fff-143e-c70a-c76bcd25729a\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">At the top of Rangko Cave, there is also a very beautiful and charming stalactite ornament. To reach Rangko Cave, it takes about 1 hour from Labuan Bajo to Rangko Village. After that you will be greeted by local residents who offer boat services to cross to the Rangko Cave. Because of the roads that are rocky and the ground that is quite slippery, you need to be careful and are advised not to use sandals. Rangko Cave has a best time to enjoy the view, which is around 12.00 - 14.00, so you should leave as early as possible from Labuan Bajo if you don\'t want to miss the moment.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201203154711.png','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 07:22:26','2020-12-23 01:25:28'),(47,1,'wae-rebo','Wae Rebo','Wae Rebo',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kampung Wae Rebo adalah sebuah kampung adat terpencil dan misterius yang terletak di Desa Satar Lenda, Kecamatan Satar Mese Barat, Kabupaten Manggarai, Provinsi Nusa Tenggara Timur. Kampung Wae Rebo berada di pegunungan &plusmn; 1200 m di atas permukaan laut, memiliki 7 rumah utama yang disebut Niang dalam bahasa Manggarai dan memiliki arsitektur yang sangat unik. Satu unit rumah dihuni oleh 7-8 keluarga, rumah ini berbentuk kerucut dan bundar serta memiliki diameter dan tinggi yang sama sama yang lain.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pada tahun 2012 Kampung Wae Rebo diakui oleh UNESCO sebagai salah satu warisan budaya dunia sebagai penghargaan bagi masyarakat lokal yang memiliki komitmen untuk menjaga dan melestarikan adat dan budaya secara turun temurun. Dari pusat kota Ruteng kampung ini berjarak &plusmn; 65 km untuk sampai Kampung Denge (kampong terakhir) di lereng pegunungan Hutan Todo dengan waktu tempuh &plusmn; 1,5 jam, kemudian dilanjutkan perjalanan trekking &plusmn; 4 jam untuk mencapai Kampung Wae Rebo di Puncak Pegunungan.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Banyak Wisatawan maupun peneliti yang berlama-lama di Wae Rebo untuk mencari tahu asal muasal dan keunikan arsitektur Mbaru Niang Wae Rebo. Untuk mencapai Wae Rebo, Anda harus menempuh perjalanan sekitar 6 km dari Desa Dintor menuju Desa Denge menggunakan motor. Tidak sampai situ, Anda masih harus melewati perjalanan dari Denge menuju Wae Rebo kurang lebih sekitar 3 jam waktu pendakian dengan pemandangan hutan lebat dan jurang. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kampung Wae Rebo is a remote and mysterious traditional village located in Satar Lenda Village, West Satar Mese District, Manggarai Regency, East Nusa Tenggara Province. Kampung Wae Rebo is in the &plusmn; 1200 m above sea level mountain. It has 7 main houses which are called Niang in Manggarai language and it has a very exclusive architecture. One house unit is inhabited by 7-8 families. This house is in a cone-shaped, round and has the same diameter and height as each other.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-9804bbd1-7fff-00cf-0d41-9acf86cac619\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In 2012, Kampung Wae Rebo was recognized by UNESCO as one of the world cultural heritages. It was a tribute to local communities for their commitment to maintain and to conserve their customs and culture from generation to generation. This village is about 65 km away from the downtown of Ruteng. To reach Kampung Denge (the last village) on the slopes of the Todo Forest mountains it takes approximately 1.5 hours travel time and then continues with a 4 hours trekking trip to arrive at Kampung Wae Rebo on the mountain top.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Many tourists and researchers have lingered at Wae Rebo to find out the origins and characteristics of Mbaru Niang Wae Rebo architecture. To reach Wae Rebo, you have to travel about 6 km from Dintor Village to Denge Village by motorbike. It doesn\'t stop there, you still have to go through a journey from Denge to Wae Rebo with approximately 3 hours of climbing time with views of dense forest and ravines. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201210083710.png','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Desa Satarlenda, Kecamatan Satarmese Barat, Kabupaten Manggarai, NTT','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,0,'2020-11-30 07:35:53','2020-12-24 11:49:26'),(58,1,'diving-spots','Diving Spots','Diving Spots',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Taman Laut Selat Pantar merupakan salah satu diving spot terkenal yang berlokasi di Kabupaten Alor, keberadaan lokasi tersebut tentunya sudah menjadi pembicaraan bagi para pelaku wisata minat khusus tersebut. Sedangkan spot Diving terkenal di Maumere adalah Taman Laut Teluk Maumere, Sebelumnya Teluk ini mengalami bencana alam pada tahun 1992, dan atas bantuan masyarakat serta pemerintah melestarikan alam bawah lautnya hingga menjadi salah satu tempat terbaik untuk melakukan diving dan masuk kedalam The Most Diving Spot dari Anugerah Pesona Indonesia (API) 2017.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Terumbu karang di dalam Selat Pantar memiliki banyak sekali ragam warna tumbuhan laut, mulai dari ungu, hijau, kuning, coklat, merah, abu-abu, jingga, dan juga putih semua warna menghiasi bawah laut. Selain itu Selat Pantar juga dihiasi dengan ikan-ikan cantik seperti flasher, alien, dan invaders yang akan memanjakan mata pengunjung yang menyaksikannya.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pantar Strait Marine Park is one of the famous diving spots located in Alor Regency, the existence of this location has certainly become a discussion for the special interest tourism actors. Meanwhile, the famous diving spot in Maumere is the Maumere Bay Marine Park. Previously, this bay experienced a natural disaster in 1992. But with the help of the community and the government, it has preserved its underwater world so that it has become one of the best places to dive and nominated for The Most Diving Spot from Anugerah Pesona Indonesia (API) 2017.</span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-742dd593-7fff-efd0-13db-9e149e18608d\"></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The coral reefs in the Pantar Strait have various colors of marine plants, ranging from purple, green, yellow, brown, red, gray, orange, and white; all colors adorn the underwater. In addition, the Pantar Strait is also decorated with adorable fish such as flashers, aliens and invaders that will spoil the eyes of visitors who witness it.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201210085318.png','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 07:59:18','2020-12-23 01:31:51'),(60,1,'desa-takpala','Desa Takpala','Takpala Village',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Desa Takpala berada di wilayah Kabupaten Alor tepatnya di Kecamatan Alor Tengah Utara, Desa Lembur Barat. Desa Takpala saat ini dianggap sebagai cagar budaya dan dilindungi berdasarkan peraturan daerah Kabupaten Alor. suku yang mendiami adalah suku Abui.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Desa ini dihuni sekitar 13 kepala keluarga Suku Abui yang tinggal di sebuah rumah adat dengan bentuk limas dan beratap ilalang. Di balik keunikan desa ini adalah, Takpala terdiri dari dua kata yaitu Tak berart tidak ada batasnya, sedangkan Pala berarti kayu. Jadi Takpala merupakan Kayu pembatas.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Desa Takpala menyimpan sejuta budaya yang unik dan menarik. Setiap pengunjung yang berkunjung ke desa ini akan disuguhkan dengan tarian tradisional yang dibawakan oleh wanita-wanita Suku Abui. Selain itu, Anda juga akan disambut dengan syair-syair lagu yang mengiringi tarian dan sekumpulan lelaki beratraksi sambil mengangkat senjata dan perisai mereka. Untuk mencapai desa ini, Anda harus melewati 21 anak tangga.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bagi pengunjung desa Takpala, Anda juga bisa menggunakan atau menyewa pakaian adat lengkap dengan aksesoris kepala dan gelang. Selain itu, Anda juga bisa menikmati latar rumah-rumah Lopo dan jangan lupa untuk mengabadikan momen.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Takpala Village is located in Alor Regency, precisely in Alor Tengah Utara District, West Lembur Village. Takpala Village is currently considered a cultural heritage and is protected under the Alor Regency regional regulation and inhabited by the Abui tribe.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-22d6ea18-7fff-cc84-f34b-703fafcd51fb\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This village is populated by around 13 heads of Abui tribe who live in a traditional house with a pyramid shape and thatched roof. Behind the catchy name of this village, Takpala actually consists of two words. \"Tak\" which means boundaries, while \"Pala\" means wood. So Takpala is a wood barrier.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Takpala Village holds a million eccentric and interesting cultures. Every visitor who visits this village will be welcomed with a traditional dance performed by Abui women. Other than that, you will also be greeted with song lyrics that accompany the dance and a group of men strutting while raising their weapons and shields. To reach this village, you have to pass 21 stairs.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">For visitors of Takpala village, you can also use or rent traditional clothes complete with head accessories and bracelets. Besides that, you can also enjoy the backgrounds of Lopo\'s houses and don\'t forget to capture the moment.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201210085445.png','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','labuan',NULL,1,'2020-11-30 08:05:06','2020-12-23 01:33:11'),(62,1,'rumah-pengasingan-soekarno','Rumah Pengasingan Soekarno','Soekarno\'s Exile House',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Terletak di jalan Perwira, Kelurahan Kotaraja Kecamatan Ende Utara (Kota Ende). Bangunan situs ini merupakan bekas rumah atau tempat tinggal Bung Karno dan keluarga semasa pembuangan/ pengasingan di Ende oleh Pemerintah Hindia Belanda tahun 1934-1938 yang masih dijaga, dirawat dan dipertahankan keasliannya oleh Pemerintah&nbsp; Kabupaten Ende. Selama di Ende, Soekarno dan keluarganya menempati sebuah rumah di tengah perumahan penduduk biasa. Pada kesempatan kunjungan yang kedua (1954), Soekarno meresmikan rumah tersebut sebagai Situs Bung Karno pada tanggal 16 Mei 1954.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-38d62b7d-7fff-558b-6e03-e89c6feff19f\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Semua barang koleksi milik Bung Karno masih tersimpan dengan baik di dalam museum ini seperti : foto keluarga, foto pribadi Bung Karno, barang keramik, dua buah tongkat berkepala monyet, pena ukuran besar, piring nasi, cerek air minum, besi setrika, alat gantungan pakaian, lemari pakaian, tempat tidur besi, lukisan- lukisan dan masih banyak barang koleksi lainnya. Di dalam Situs Rumah Bung Karno juga terdapat tempat sujud/ruang semedi dan tempat sembahyang/sholat yang selalu digunakan oleh Bung Karno bersujud kepada Tuhan Yang Maha Esa untuk memohon bantuan bagi Perjuangan Kemerdekaan bangsa Indonesia hingga membekas di lantai. Dan di belakang museum Bung Karno terdapat sebuah sumur dengan kedalaman 12 meter yang digunakan oleh Bung Karno untuk mandi, cuci dan minum serta wudhu. Konon air sumur ini dipercaya mempunyai khasiat untuk penyembuhan berbagai penyakit dan bisa membuat&nbsp; orang menjadi awet muda.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This house is located on Perwira Street, Kotaraja Village, North Ende District (Ende City). This site building is the former house or residence of Bung Karno and his family during the exile in Ende by the Dutch East Indies Government in 1934-1938. Until now, the asset house is still protected, cared for and maintained its authenticity by the Ende Regency Government. While in Ende, Soekarno and his family lived in a house in the middle of ordinary people\'s housing. On the occasion of his second visit (1954), Soekarno inaugurated the house as the Bung Karno Site on May 16, 1954.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-5abda737-7fff-2bc9-46f0-24f7f20d9171\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">All Bung Karno\'s collections are still well kept in this museum, such as: family photos, Bung Karno\'s personal photos, ceramics, two sticks with the head of a monkey, a large pen, a rice plate, a drinking water kettle, an iron, a clothes hanger, a wardrobe, an iron bed, paintings and many other collectibles. In the Bung Karno Home Site there is also a prostration room or meditation room and a place of prayer which is always used by Bung Karno to prostrate to God Almighty, asking for help for the Indonesian independence struggle until a mark is left on the floor. On the back of Bung Karno museum there is a well with a depth of 12 meters which is used by Bung Karno for bathing, washing and drinking as well as </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">wudhu</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (ablution before praying). It is said that that well water is now believed to have properties for healing various diseases and can make people stay young.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Jl. Perwira, Kel. Kotaraja, Ende Utara, Kabupaten Ende, Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-12-24 00:14:58','2020-12-24 00:15:05'),(63,1,'ikat-weaving-village','Ikat Weaving Village','Ikat Weaving Village',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pewarnaan ikat atau benang adalah teknik kuno Indonesia yang dapat dilihat di banyak desa di Flores. Pola tenun ikat ditentukan oleh tradisi dan diwariskan dari generasi ke generasi dan proses menenunnya masih diiringi dengan pertunjukan dan upacara adat.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pemandangan wanita muda dan tua menenun ikat dapat Anda lihat di banyak desa di Flores. Tenun ikat di Flores sendiri berasal dari daerah Sikka di pantai selatan Flores dan merupakan satu-satunya kerajinan yang luar biasa di Flores. Teknik ikat sendiri adalah kapas yang direntangkan pada rangka yang terbuat dari bambu dan dibuat sesuai dengan pola yang diinginkan. Kemudian, untuk proses pewarnaan dibutuhkan beberapa kali pengulangan warna. Hal ini menandakan bahwa 1 proses membutuhkan waktu berminggu-minggu bahkan bertahun-tahun tergantung dengan tingkat kesulitan.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Selain itu, di desa ini Anda bisa menemukan tenun ikat yang tradisional dimana kapas yang dipintal masih menggunakan tangan dan warna alami. Saat ini, kain ikat milik desa masih menjadi pakaian sehari-hari oleh para Wanita desa dan juga pakaian adat untuk acara-acara perayaan hari besar atau gereja hari Minggu.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Tie or yarn dyeing is an ancient Indonesian technique that can be seen in many villages in Flores. The weaving pattern is determined by tradition and passed down from generation to generation. The weaving process is still accompanied by traditional performances and ceremonies.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-e79601e3-7fff-6f4e-6888-15057f6ca90c\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You can see the sight of young and old women weaving Ikat in many villages in Flores. The weaving in Flores originates from the Sikka area on the south coast of Flores and is the only outstanding handicraft on Flores. The tie technique itself is cotton which is stretched on a frame made of bamboo and made according to the desired pattern. Then, for the coloring process it takes several repetitions of color. This indicates that a process could take weeks or even years depending on the level of difficulty.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In this village you can find traditional Ikat weaving where the cotton is spun by hand and natural colors as well. Currently, the village-owned Ikat cloth is still used as daily clothes by village women and is also traditional clothing for holidays or Sunday church events.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224002026.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-12-24 00:20:26','2020-12-24 00:20:53'),(64,2,'taman-nasional-kelimutu','Taman Nasional Kelimutu','Kelimutu National Park',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Taman Nasional Kelimutu terletak di Flores. Di Taman Nasional Kelimutu yang berlokasi di Kabupaten Ende merupakan tempat wisata yang sudah terkenal hingga dunia Internasional. keunikannya adalah tiga danau yang ada memiliki warna yang berbeda, warna itu dipengaruhi oleh mikroba yang ada di tiap danau serta suhu gas sehingga mempengaruhi warna yang terbentuk. Danau berwarna hijau lumut dinamakan Tiwu Nuwa Muri Kofai dengan kedalaman kurang lebih 127 Meter dan luas 5.5 Ha. Danau berwarna hijau yaitu Tiwu Ata Polo memiliki kedalaman kurang lebih 64 Meter dengan luas 4.5 Ha dan warnanya sering berubah-ubah. lalu yang terakhir adalah Tiwu Ata Mbupu dengan kedalaman kurang lebih 67 Meter dengan luas 4 Ha.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Jika Anda ingin berkunjung ke Taman Nasional Kelimutu untuk mendapatkan pemandangan terbaik, berangkatlah di antara bulan Juni - Agustus karena cuaca cenderung cerah dan tidak hujan. Sehingga medan yang dilewati aman, mengingat jalannya yang dipisahkan oleh tebing batu curam dan mudah longsor. Sedangkan untuk waktu, disarankan untuk berangkat mendaki di antara jam 2 - 3 pagi dari Moni yang merupakan desa terdekat dari Taman Nasional Kelimutu.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Selain menikmati pemandangan danau, Anda juga bisa menikmati lokasi langsung dari habitat beberapa jenis binatang dan tumbuhan yang hampir punah. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kelimutu National Park is located in Flores. In Kelimutu National Park, which is located in Ende Regency, is a tourist spot that is well known to the international world. It is amazing that the three lakes have different colors, which is influenced by the microbes present in each lake and the temperature of the gas so that it affects the color that is formed. The lake in moss green color is called Tiwu Ko\'o Fai Nuwa Muri with a depth of approximately 127 meters and an area of ​​5.5 hectares. The green lake, namely Tiwu Ata Polo, has a depth of approximately 64 meters with an area of ​​4.5 hectares and the color often changes. Then, the last one is Tiwu Ata Mbupu which usually has a blue color with a depth of approximately 67 meters with an area of ​​4 hectares.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you want to visit Kelimutu National Park for the best views, go between June - August as the weather tends to be sunny and not rainy. So that the terrain that is traversed is safe, considering the road is separated by steep rock cliffs and is prone to landslides. As for time, it is recommended to go for a hike between 2 - 3 am from Moni which is the closest village to the Kelimutu National Park.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Besides enjoying the view of the lake, you can also enjoy the direct location of the habitat for several endangered species of animals and plants. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224002352.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Flores, Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-12-24 00:23:52','2020-12-24 00:23:59'),(65,1,'phinisi','Phinisi','Phinisi',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Mau mencoba </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Life on Board</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> a la film Hollywood? Tenang, sekarang Anda bisa menikmatinya dengan mencoba Phinisi di Labuan Bajo. Phinisi merupakan kapal tradisional asli Indonesia berasal dari Kabupaten Bulukumba Sulsel. Kapal Phinisi mulai berdatangan ke Labuan Bajo dan banyak yang sudah dimodifikasi dari bentuk asli ke bentuk phinisi yang lebih cocok untuk keperluan wisatawan.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Jika Anda tertarik, jangan lupa untuk mencari terlebih dahulu berapa biaya kisaran kapal Phinisi ini. Karena, beda pengelola biasanya beda fasilitas kapal. Tapi, pada umumnya kapal Phinisi dilengkapi hingga 14 kamar dengan masing-masing kamar diisi oleh 2 orang. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Want to try life on board just like in a Hollywood movie? Relax, you can now experience it by hopping on Phinisi in Labuan Bajo. Phinisi is a traditional Indonesian ship originating from Bulukumba Regency, South Sulawesi. Phinisi ships began arriving at Labuan Bajo and many have been modified from their original phinisi form to a novel phinisi form which is more suitable for tourist needs.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-fc53fa85-7fff-6f92-ee5f-d2385c55c7a9\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you\'re interested, don\'t forget to look up in advance how much this phinisi range costs. The reason is different managers usually have different ship facilities. However, mostly the Phinisi ships are equipped with up to 14 rooms with each room can be filled by 2 people. </span></span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224022530.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Labuan Bajo','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-12-24 02:25:30','2020-12-24 02:27:10'),(66,1,'pantai-lariti','Pantai Lariti','Lariti Beach',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pantai Lariti merupakan salah satu destinasi wisata baru di Nusa Tenggara Barat. Lokasinya berada di Kabupaten Bima, tidak jauh dari Pelabuhan Sape. Pantai yang memiliki keindahan panorama yang menawan ini merupakan gerbang laut yang menghubungkan ujung Pulau Sumbawa dan Pulau Flores. Diperlukan waktu tempuh sekitar 1 jam untuk sampai di pantai cantik ini jika Anda berangkat dari Kabupaten Bima.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pantai Lariti memiliki pasir putih cantik dan merupakan destinasi yang baru saja dibuka untuk publik. Di seberang Pulau Lariti, terdapat sebuah pulau kecil bernama Nisa Lampa Jara dengan spot menarik untuk menikmati pemandangan laut dan gunung. Saat air laut sedang surut, maka Pulau Lariti dan Pulau Nisa Lampa Jara akan terhubung melalui sebuah jembatan pasir yang dapat ditempuh&nbsp; dengan jalan kaki.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lariti Beach is a new tourist destination in West Nusa Tenggara. The location is in Bima Regency, not far from Sape Harbor. This beach, which has a charming panoramic beauty, is a sea gate that connects the tip of Sumbawa Island and Flores Island. It takes about 1 hour to arrive at this lovely beach if you depart from Bima Regency.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-20e6d126-7fff-06f6-1bc9-1284286613cd\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lariti Beach has captivating white sand and it is a destination that has recently opened for the public. Across the Lariti Island, there is a small island called Nisa Lampa Jara with an interesting spot to relish the sea and the mountain views. When the sea water recedes, Lariti Island and Nisa Lampa Jara Island will be connected through a sand bridge that can be reached by foot.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224023423.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Desa Soro, Kecamatan Lambu, Kabupaten Bima, NTB','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-12-24 02:34:23','2020-12-24 02:36:14'),(67,1,'pantai-ular','Pantai Ular','Snake Beach',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pantai Ular adalah salah satu pantai yang berada di Desa Pai, Kabupaten Bima. Pantai Ular memiliki sejarah panjang mengenai perjuangan rakyat Bima dalam melawan agresi Belanda. Pulau ini terkenal dengan cerita kutukan seorang dukun setempat kepada orang-orang Belanda yang menjajah tanahnya. Masyarakat percaya jika kutukan tersebut telah merubah para penjajah menjadi ular dan hidup selamanya di pulau tersebut sehingga tidak pernah dapat bebas.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pulau Ular ini adalah batu karang yang memiliki luas kurang lebih 800 meter persegi. Jika biasanya, batu karang menjadi tempat tinggal ikan atau tumbuhan laut. Di pulau ini menjadi tempat tinggal ratusan ular, oleh sebab itu, pulau ini dijuluki Pulau Ular oleh warga sekitar. Ular-ular tersebut adalah ular beracun dan pengunjung tidak boleh sembarangan memegang ular tersebut, terlebih membawanya ke luar pulau.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Jika kamu tertarik untuk berkunjung ke pulau ini, pastikan untuk menjaga keselamatan diri dan mematuhi peraturan yang ada, ya.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Snake Beach Snake Beach is one of the beaches in Pai Village, Bima Regency. Ular Beach has a long history of the struggle of the Bima people against Dutch aggression. This island is famous for the story of the curse of a local shaman to the Dutch who colonized the land. The people believed that the curse had turned the invaders into snakes and lived forever on the island so that they could never be free.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Snake Island is a rock that has an area of ​​approximately 800 square meters. If usually, the rock is a habitat for fish or marine plants. The island is home to hundreds of snakes, therefore, the island is nicknamed Snake Island by local residents. iThe snakes are poisonous snakes and visitors must not carelessly hold the snake, especially taking it outside the island.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you are interested in visiting this island, make sure to keep yourself safe and comply with the existing rules, yes.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224023858.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','JL Payi Sape, RT. 07 / RW. 03, Wera, Sarae, Rasanae Bar., Bima, Nusa Tenggara Bar','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4',1,'2020-12-24 02:38:58','2020-12-24 02:39:45'),(68,1,'pulau-kelapa','Pulau Kelapa','Kelapa Island',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bukan Indonesia namanya, jika tidak memiliki sejuta pulau indah yang tersembunyi. Salah satunya ada Nisa Lampu, atau yang lebih dikenal dengan nama Pulau Kelapa. Pulau ini terletak di Selat Sape, sebelah timur Kabupaten Bima. Yang menjadi unik adalah, jika dilihat dari sekilas pemandangan Pulau Bima sangat mirip dengan pemandangan di Raja Ampat.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pulau ini memiliki bukit-bukit yang ditutupi rumput dan padang savana. Gugusan terumbu karang yang indah dapat dilihat dari atas Pulau Kelapa. Untuk dapat melihat pemandangannya, Anda harus menanjak sekitar 30 menit untuk sampai di atas bukit. Untuk itu, jangan lupa membawa sepatu trekking dan baju yang nyaman, ya!</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c9f0466f-7fff-6881-e174-5c48bb22c261\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">It\'s not Indonesia, if it doesn\'t have millions of beautiful hidden islands. One of them is Nisa Lampu, or better known as Kelapa Island. The island is located in the Sape Strait, east of Bima Regency. What makes this island special is at first glance, the view of Bima Island is very similar to the view of the famous Raja Ampat.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The island has hills covered with grass and savanna. Beautiful coral reefs can be seen from the top of Kelapa Island. To be able to see the view, you have to climb about 30 minutes to get to the top of the hill. For that, don\'t forget to bring comfortable trekking shoes and clothes, OK!</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224114332.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Pulau Kelapa, Labuan Bajo, Manggarai Barat, NTT','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,1,'2020-12-24 11:43:32','2020-12-24 11:43:45'),(69,1,'manggarai-liang-bua','Manggarai (Liang Bua)','Manggarai (Liang Bua)',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ada yang merasa asing dengan daerah Liang Bua? Atau justru sudah sangat familiar? Liang Bua merupakan salah satu situs gua yang berada di Dusun Rampasasa, Desa Liang Bua, Kecamatan Wae Ri\'i. Gua Liang Gua merupakan tempat ditemukannya \" Homo Florensis\" atau manusia Flores purba dengan tinggi hanya 100 cm dan berat 25 kg.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-caf69c2b-7fff-4c7a-7150-591dd005c104\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Secara morfologi, Liang Bua memiliki ciri sebagai hunian pada masa prasejarah. Hal ini dapat dilihat dari ukuran gua yang dalam dan lebar atap yang tinggi, serta lantai gua yang luas dan relatif datar. Selain itu, hal ini juga diperkuat dengan lokasi gua sendiri yang sangat dekat dengan aliran sungai (Sungai Wae Racang dan Wae Mulu), sebagai sumber kebutuhan hidup penghuninya.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sampai saat ini Pusat Penelitian Arkeologi Nasional secara berkelanjutan tetap melakukan penelitian di Situs Liang Bua.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Does anyone feel unfamiliar with the Liang Bua area? Or are they very familiar? Liang Bua is one of the cave sites located in Rampasasa Hamlet, Liang Bua Village, Wae Ri\'i District. Liang Cave is the place where the </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Homo Floresiensis</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> or ancient Flores man with a height of only 100 cm and a weight of 25 kg was discovered.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d44b7718-7fff-829c-e88b-39f4d0f6b174\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Morphologically, Liang Bua is characterized as a prehistoric dwelling. This can be seen from the deep size of the cave and the width of the high roof, as well as the broad and relatively flat floor of the cave. Moreover, this is also reinforced by the location of the cave itself which is very close to the river (Wae Racang and Wae Mulu Rivers), as a source of living needs for the inhabitants.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Until now, the National Archaeological Research Center continues to conduct research at the Liang Bua Site.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224114843.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Dusun Rampasasa, Desa Liang Bua, Kecamatan Rahong Utara','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 11:48:43','2020-12-24 11:48:43'),(70,1,'danau-rana-tonjong','Danau Rana Tonjong','Rana Tonjong Lake',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Danau Rana Tonjong yang terletak di Pota merupakan danau yang seluruh permukaannya ditumbuhi bunga teratai raksasa/giant lotus atau tonjong dalam bahasa setempat. Bahkan, Danau Rana Tonjong merupakan salah satu danau teratai terbesar di dunia. Danau ini terletak di Desa Nangabaras, Sambirampas, Manggarai Timur.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bunga teratai itu hanya berbunga sekali setahun pada bulan April dan Mei. Di dalam bunga yang sudah mekar terdapat biji-bijian yang dapat dimakan mentah dan memiliki rasa seperti kacang tanah. Bunga teratai ini dipercaya tidak dapat tumbuh dan berbunga di tempat lain selain di danau itu. Rana Tonjong menjadi habitat bagi ikan air tawar, katak, dan tempat mencari makan bagi burung angsa putih.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Siapa pun yang berkunjung ke danau ini dijamin akan berdecak kagum dengan keindahan bunga teratai yang disajikan. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Rana Tonjong Lake in Pota, is a lake whose entire surface is covered with giant lotus or </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">tonjong</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> in the local language. In fact, Rana Tonjong Lake is one of the largest lotus lakes in the world. This lake is located in Nangabaras Village, Sambirampas, East Manggarai.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f031fc32-7fff-8624-7152-4a690241a2b7\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The lotus flower only blooms once a year in April and May. Inside the blooming flower, there are seeds that can be eaten raw and taste like peanuts. This lotus flower is believed to be unable to grow and blossom anywhere other than in the Rana Tonjong Lake. The lake is also a habitat for freshwater fish, frogs and a place to find food for white swans.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Anyone who visits this lake is guaranteed to be amazed by the beauty of the lotus flowers that are presented. </span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224115117.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Desa Nangabaras, Sambirampas, Manggarai Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 11:51:17','2020-12-24 11:51:17'),(71,1,'teluk-nanga-lok','Teluk Nanga Lok','Nanga Lok Bay',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Nanga Lok merupakan salah satu teluk dangkal di ujung utara Kabupaten Manggarai Timur. Teluk Nanga Lok sebuah teluk yang begitu cantik, terbingkai oleh perbukitan savana yang mengelilinginya. Pemandangan pepohonan bakau yang memenuhi bagian pinggir pantai justru membuat paduan alam yang sangat sempurna. Warna biru kehijauan air laut menandakan bahwa pantai tersebut masih sangat bersih.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Waktu yang tepat untuk berkunjung ke Teluk Nanga Lok adalah sore hari. Karena, sinar matahari yang sudah mulai turun sehingga tidak terlalu panas dan menyengat kulit.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Nanga Lok is a shallow bay at the northern tip of East Manggarai Regency. Nanga Lok Bay is a very beautiful bay, framed by the savanna hills that surround it. The view of mangrove trees that fill the beach makes a perfect blend of nature. The turquoise color of the sea water indicates that the beach is still very clean.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-04e2cde6-7fff-fb28-1b7c-c81fb6bfe3c3\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The best time to visit Nanga Lok Bay is in the afternoon. The reason is the sun\'s rays have started to fall so it doesn\'t get too hot and sting to the skin.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224115301.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Borong, Kabupaten Manggarai Timur, Flores, Provinsi Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 11:53:01','2020-12-24 11:53:01'),(72,1,'komodo-rughu','Komodo Rughu','Komodo Rughu',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kalau biasanya Anda hanya mengenal pulaunya, mari kita berkenalan dengan penghuninya. Keunikan Komodo di Manggarai Timur terletak pada warna kulit dan bentuk tubuhnya. Warna kulitnya lebih terang dan didominasi warna coklat dan kuning keemasan. Sosoknya lebih ramping, meski panjang tubuhnya sama dengan yang ada di Komodo. Taman Nasional yang berukuran lebih besar dan sisik berwarna coklat tua.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Komodo yang dikenal dengan nama Rughu dalam bahasa setempat berada dalam masalah serius. Populasi tersebut terancam punah karena beberapa faktor yang mempengaruhi perkembangannya. Beberapa faktor tersebut antara lain sumber pangan yang terbatas, perburuan liar, dan alih fungsi lahan menjadi lahan pertanian. Jika kita tidak memperhatikan masalah ini, cepat atau lambat Komodo di kawasan ini akan punah.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Mari jaga kelestarian habitat Komodo ini dengan tidak merusak rumah mereka dan terus menjaga alam sekitar.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you usually know the island only, let\'s get acquainted with the inhabitants. The characteristics of Komodo dragons in East Manggarai lies in their skin color and body shape. The skin color is lighter, predominantly brown and golden yellow. His figure is slimmer, even though his body length is the same as ones from the Komodo National Park which is larger and has dark brown scales.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-fc335740-7fff-5cb4-da30-da25ceca311a\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Komodo dragon, known as Rughu in the local language, is in serious trouble. This population is threatened with extinction due to several factors that influence its development. Some of these factors include limited food sources, illegal hunting, and land conversion into agricultural land. If we don\'t pay attention to this problem, sooner or later the Komodo dragons in this area will become extinct.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Let\'s protect the Komodo dragon\'s habitat by not destroying their homes and continuing to protect the surrounding environment.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224115630.png','https://www.youtube.com/embed/3GYqJdLJa_4','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Pulau Komodo, Kabupaten Manggarai Barat, Nusa Tenggara Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 11:56:29','2020-12-24 11:56:30'),(73,1,'kopi-colol','Kopi Colol','Colol Coffee',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Desa Colol di Kecamatan Poco Ranaka Timur, Kabupaten Manggarai Timur (Matim) sejak lama dikenal sebagai daerah penghasil kopi. Kini desa ini ditetapkan sebagai desa wisata berbasis kopi. Kopi Colol menjadi salah satu daya tarik wisatawan dan mata pencaharian dari warga kampung tersebut.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-db8f85bf-7fff-8b5b-c097-36de90310c40\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ada tiga jenis kopi yang tersedia di Desa Colol, yaitu Kopi Arabika, Kopi Juria, dan Yellow Kopi. Dalam satu sahun, Desa Cololo bisa memproduksi sekitar 500 ton. Hal ini bisa menjadi potensi yang besar untuk mendistribusikan Kopi Colol ke seluruh penjuru Indonesia.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Colol Village in Poco Ranaka Timur District, East Manggarai Regency (Matim) has long been known as a coffee producing area. Now this village is entitled as a coffee-based tourism village. Colol coffee is one of the tourist attractions and the livelihoods of the residents of the village.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4aa09f9b-7fff-fff9-17c7-d66489b9f457\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There are three types of coffee available in Colol Village, there are Arabica Coffee, Juria Coffee, and Yellow Kopi. In one year, Colol Village can produce around 500 tons of coffee. This could be a huge potential to distribute Colol Coffee throughout Indonesia.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224135739.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Kopi Colol di Kampung Biting, Desa Uluwae, Kecamatan Poco Ranaka Timur, Manggarai Timur, NTT','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 13:57:39','2020-12-24 13:57:39'),(74,1,'kampung-adat-bena-kampung-adat-tololela-dan-kampung-adat-gurusina','Kampung Adat Bena, Kampung Adat Tololela, Dan Kampung Adat Gurusina','Bena Traditional Village, Tololela Traditional Village and Gurusina Traditional Village',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kampung Adat Bena, Kampung Adat Tololela dan Kampung Adat Gurusina merupakan kampung adat yang terletak di Lembah Jerebu\'u, Bajawa. Ketiga kampung adat ini terkenal dengan rumah adat dan tradisi nenek moyangnya.&nbsp; Terletak di kaki Gunung Inerie dan dikelilingi bambu dan pohon beringin yang begitu rimbun menjadi ciri khas dari kampung tua ini. Saat memasuki perkampungan, kita akan disuguhkan pemandangan rumah-rumah tradisional yang berbentuk unik, terbuat dari kayu dengan menggunakan ilalang sebagai atap. Rumah&ndash;rumah di perkampungan adat ini dibangun dengan mempertahankan kontur asli tanah. Oleh karena itu, bentuk kampung nampak berundak-undak.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Uniknya formasi rumah ini tersusun rapi membentuk pola segi empat, di mana bagian tengahnya terdapat lapangan berundak yang digunakan sebagai tempat Ngadu dan Bhaga. Selain itu juga ada kuburan batu tua yang diletakkan di tengah lapangan. Di setiap rumah-rumah kampung adat ini dapat ditemukan tanduk kerbau yang dulunya dijadikan kurban untuk upacara adat penduduk setempat.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b9729b9c-7fff-5134-01bd-29f8ff655af5\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bena Traditional Village, Tololela Traditional Village and Gurusina Traditional Village are traditional villages located in the Jerebu\'u Valley, Bajawa. These three traditional villages are famous for their traditional houses and traditions of their ancestors. Located at the foot of Mount Inerie and surrounded by lush bamboo and banyan trees, it is the hallmark of this old village. When entering the village, we will be served with the view of astonishing traditional houses made of wood using thatch as roofs. The houses in this traditional village are built keeping the original contours of the land. Therefore, the form of the village appears to be terraced.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">What makes it interesting is the formation of this house is neatly arranged in a rectangular pattern, where in the middle there is a terraced field which is used as a place for Ngadu and Bhaga. Besides that, there is also an old stone grave that is placed in the middle of the field. In each of the houses of this traditional village, you can find buffalo horns which were used as sacrifices for traditional ceremonies of the local population.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>',NULL,'s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 14:01:43','2020-12-24 14:01:43'),(75,1,'semana-santa','Semana Santa','Semana Santa',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Semana Santa adalah ritual perayaan Pekan Suci Paskah yang dilakukan selama 7 hari berturut-turut oleh umat Katolik di Larantuka. Festival Tahunan yang rutin di selenggarakan di Flores Timur kota Larantuka, festival ini sudah dilaksanakan lebih dari setengah abad lalu dan merupakan perayaan sakral Paskah bagi umat Katolik di Larantuka. sebelum festival ini ada festival Bale Nagi (Pulang Kampung) bagi mereka yang merayakan untuk kembali pulang dan merayakan bersama keluarga besar mereka.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pekan Suci Semana Santa biasanya dimulai dari Minggu Palma, Rabu Abu, Kamis Putih, Jumat Agung, Sabtu Suci, hingga Minggu Paskah. Jika Anda tertarik ingin menyaksikan proses Semana Santa sebaiknya untuk melakukan booking penginapan jauh-jauh hari.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Semana Santa is a ritual to celebrate the Holy Week of Easter which is carried out for 7 consecutive days by Catholics in Larantuka. The annual festival which is regularly held in the East Flores city of Larantuka has been held for more than half a century and is a sacred Easter celebration for Catholics in Larantuka. Before this festival is held, there is a Bale Nagi (Returning Village) festival for those who celebrate to return home and celebrate with their extended family.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-fe3971ec-7fff-8000-4e4b-11b9a70127e7\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Semana Santa Holy Week usually starts from Palm Sunday, Ash Wednesday, Holy Thursday, Good Friday, Holy Saturday, to Easter Sunday. If you are interested in witnessing the Semana Santa process, it is best to book accommodation in advance.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224140353.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Flores Timur','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 14:03:53','2020-12-24 14:03:53'),(76,1,'bukit-doa','Bukit Doa','Hill of Contemplation',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bukit Doa Watomiten atau dikenal dengan Bukit Kontemplasi merupakan salah satu dari destinasi wisata integrated Bukit Cinta Lembata (BCL) yang memiliki pemandangan alam&nbsp; pantai dan bukit yang eksotis. Bukit Doa Watomiten terletak di Desa Bour, Kecamatan Nubatukan, Kabupaten Lembata dengan jarak tempuh dari pusat kota Lewoleba sekitar 19KM dan dapat ditempuh dengan waktu kurang lebih 30 menit menggunakan kendaraan roda dua maupun roda empat.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ketika dalam perjalanan menuju Bukit Doa Watomiten Pengunjung disajikan pemandangan perbukitan yang luas serta ombak pantai yang menawan. Letaknya yang jauh dari keramaian kota menjadikan Bukit Doa Watomiten sangat hening dan asri. Di sepanjang pendakian Bukit Doa Watomiten terdapat 14 ukiran patung yang artistik simbol 14 stasi (Perhentian) sehingga pengunjung dapat melakukan ibadat/doa Jalan Salib sambil menikmati semilir angin perbukitan seiring doa yang mengalir. Di puncak Bukit Doa Watomiten terdapat Patung Bunda Maria Segala Bangsa yang megah. Terdapat juga bangunan rumah ibadah dan fasilitas lainnya. Bukit Doa Watomiten sangat cocok bagi pengunjung yang ingin berwisata sambil berziarah sekaligus menikmati kemegahan dan keindahan ciptaan Tuhan yang dapat diabadikan terlebih bagi pecinta fotography/videography.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bukit Doa Watomiten or known as the Hill of Contemplation is one of the integrated tourist destinations of Bukit Cinta Lembata (BCL) which has exotic natural views of beaches and hills. Watomiten Prayer Hill is located in Bour Village, Nubatu Subdistrict, Lembata Regency, with a distance of about 19 km from downtown Lewoleba and can be reached in approximately 30 minutes using two-wheeled or four-wheeled vehicles.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b6476f3-7fff-dc2e-c7d1-53fb908feddc\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">While on the way to Watomiten Prayer Hill, visitors will be shown a wide view of the hills and charming beach waves. Located far from the city crowd, the Watomiten Prayer Hill is very quiet and graceful. Along the ascent of the Watomiten Prayer Hill there are 14 carvings of artistic symbols of 14 stations (stops) so that visitors can pray for the Way of the Cross while enjoying the hilly breeze as the prayers flow. At the top of the Watomiten Prayer Hill there is a magnificent statue of the Virgin Mary of All Nations. There are also buildings of worship and other facilities. Watomiten Prayer Hill is perfect for visitors who want to travel and have a pilgrimage while enjoying the splendor and beauty of God\'s creation that can be captured, especially for photography or videography enthusiasts.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224140612.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','iangdua, Nubatukan, Watokobu, Lembata, Kabupaten Lembata, Nusa Tenggara Tim.','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 14:06:11','2020-12-24 14:06:12'),(77,1,'lamalera-whale-catching','Lamalera Whale Catching','Lamalera Whale Catching',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lamalera Whale Catching merupakan tradisi turun temurun yang sangat unik di Kabupaten Lembata. Akan tetapi, tradisi unik ini tidak dilakukan setiap hari. Melainkan diawal dengan seremonial pada 29 April - 1 Mei sebagai pembuka prosesi. Kemudian dilanjutkan dengan adanya ritual adat di batu paus yang diyakini mampu mendatangkan kemurahan rezeki. Pada seremonial ini, tidak semua paus diburu, seperti paus biru yang memang disakralkan oleh masyarakat dan paus yang sedang hamil tidak akan diburu.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Kegiatan ini menggunakan alat tradisional hanya terdapat di desa Lamalera di Kecamatan Wulandoni sehingga destinasi tersebut dijadikan brand Destinasi Kabupaten Lembata. Jenis ikan paus yang ditangkap adalah paus sperma (Physeter macrocephalus) dan tradisi ini tidak dimiliki oleh daerah lain karena merupakan tradisi turun temurun yang masih tetap dijaga oleh nelayan Lamalera. Desa Lamalera terletak kurang lebih 52 km dari kota Lewoleba yang dapat ditempuh menggunakan kendaraan roda empat atau roda dua kurang lebih&nbsp; 3 jam perjalanan. Waktu yang terbaik untuk berkunjung ke Lamalera yakni pada musim penangkapan ikan paus pada bulan Mei sampai dengan bulan September.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pengunjung yang berwisata ke Desa Lamalera akan disuguhi berbagai rangkaian atraksi budaya yang unik sebelum musim melaut (Leva Nuang) yang diawali dengan beberapa atraksi seperti Tobu Nama Fata yang artinya musyawarah adat penyelesaian masalah antar suku yang dilaksanakan pada tanggal 28 April, ritual memanggil ikan paus di batu Paus oleh tuan tanah yang disebut Ie Gerek dilakukan pada tanggal 29 april dan arwah nelayan Lamalera yang meninggal di laut melalui Misa Arwah dan Misa Leva pada tanggal 1 Mei yang adalah upacara pembukaan musim melaut yang ditandai dengan pemberkatan peralatan tradisional untuk penangkapan ikan paus. Pengunjung akan mendapatkan pengalaman terbaik dan tak terlupakan dari Desa Lamalera dengan mengabadikan foto yang fantastis serta kekinian selama berwisata. Pengunjung dapat berbelanja oleh-oleh berupa sarung atau selendang tenun ikat di kelompok kerajinan lokal Desa Lamalera. Pengembangan infrastruktur wisata dan akses ke destinasi wisata masih dalam pembenahan untuk lebih baik sehingga dapat menjadi salah satu destinasi unggulan di Kabupaten Lembata.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lamalera Whale Catching is an epic hereditary tradition in Lembata Regency. However, this distinctive tradition is not practiced every day. It begins with a ceremony on April 29 until May 1 as the opening of the procession. Then proceed with the customary ritual on the whale stone which is believed to be able to bring good luck. At this ceremony, not all whales are hunted. For example blue whales which are sacred by the public and pregnant whales will not be hunted.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d8a51e9-7fff-9ed3-0435-85207d959f3c\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This activity only uses traditional tools and being held only&nbsp; in Lamalera village, Wulandoni District, so that the destination is used as a brand for Lembata Regency. The type of whale to catch is </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">physeter macrocephalus</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (sperm whale) and this tradition is not shared by other regions because it is a hereditary tradition that is still guarded by the fishermen of Lamalera. Lamalera Village is located approximately 52 km from the town of Lewoleba which can be reached by using a four-wheeled vehicle or two-wheeled vehicle for about 3 hours drive. The best time to visit Lamalera is during the whaling season from May to September.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Visitors who travel to Lamalera Village will be treated to a variety of unique cultural attractions before the fishing season (Leva Nuang) which begins with several attractions such as Tobu Nama Fata which means customary deliberation for inter-tribal problem solving which is held on April 28. The ritual of calling whales in The Pope\'s stone by a landlord called Ie Gerek was carried out on April 29 and the spirits of the Lamalera fishermen who died at sea through the Spirit Mass and Leva Mass on May 1, which is the opening ceremony of the fishing season marked by the blessing of traditional whaling equipment. Visitors will get the best and unforgettable experience of Lamalera Village by capturing fantastic and contemporary photos while traveling. Visitors can shop for souvenirs in the form of sarongs or woven shawls at the local handicraft group of Lamalera Village. The development of tourism infrastructure and access to tourist destinations is still being improved so that it can become one of the leading destinations in Lembata Regency.</span></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20201224140849.png',NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><em>work in progress</em></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Lamalera, Kabupaten Lembata','s.boplbf@gmail.com','09.00 - 15.00','0385 41170','beyond',NULL,0,'2020-12-24 14:08:49','2020-12-24 14:08:49'),(80,3,'pantai-mali','Pantai Mali',NULL,NULL,'<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>Kabupaten Alor adalah sebuah kabupaten di Provinsi Nusa Tenggara Timur, Indonesia. Ibu kota Alor adalah Kalabahi. Penduduk Alor berjumlah sekitar 211.872 jiwa (2020), sedangkan luasnya adalah 2.928,88 km&sup2;. Kabupaten ini berbentuk kepulauan dan dilintasi jalur pelayaran dagang internasional ke Samudera Pasifik. Kabupaten Alor merupakan salah satu dari 11 Kabupaten Koordinatif Badan Pelaksana Otorita Labuan Bajo Flores (BPOLBF) dalam rangka percepatan dan sinkronisasi percepatan pengembangan pariwisata terintegrasi di wilayah Flores, Alor, Lembata, dan Bima (Floratama). Seluruh wilayah Kabupaten Alor masuk dalam kategori iklim sabana tropis (Aw). Dalam jangka waktu setahun, durasi musim penghujan berlangsung relatif cukup singkat, yakni dari bulan Desember hingga bulan Maret, sedangkan musim kemarau mempunyai periode yang cukup panjang yakni &ge;7 bulan. Oleh karena iklimnya yang cukup kering, periode hari hujan per satu bulannya biasanya &le;20 hari. Suhu udara di wilayah Kabupaten Alor berkisar antara 21&deg;&ndash;33 &deg;C dengan tingkat kelembapan nisbi sebesar &plusmn;74%. Alor memiliki&nbsp; banyak potensi wisata, baik bahari, alam, mauoun budaya. Keindahan di darat dan di bawah lautnya begitu penuh kejutan sekaligus mengagumkan mulai dari taman bawah laut, budaya moko, suku tradisional di pegunungan, pesona Mawar Si Dugong, Hiu Tikus, hingga Al-Quran tertua di Asia Tenggara.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','thumb_20221025070546.png','-','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>-</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','-','boplbf@outlook.com','-','-','labuan','-',1,'2022-10-25 07:05:46','2022-10-25 07:17:14');
